  "text": "In 1974 [CITATION_1] ? Colloquium participants acknowledged that this double-edged sword could persist as a complication in resolving problems with reproducibility. Positive forms of competition incentivize the quest for new knowledge or the creation of a particular product. Negative competition-where competition dictates job security or the ability to continue practicing science-can impair creativity and spawn undesirable research practices.",
